<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190403>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Aulites crosnieri sp. nov., Norfolk Ridge, Norfolk 1 Stn DW 1724, 200 – 291 m: A, dorsal view of young specimen, paratype, MNHN BRA- 3137; B – E, paratype, MNHN BRA- 3138, B, C, dorsal view of complete specimen and enlargement of the umbonal part to show details of the beak, D, E, interior views to show crura and septum (D) and teeth without dental plates (E); F – J, complete specimen, holotype, MNHN BRA- 3136, F, G, ventral and dorsal views and tilted ventral view (H) to show details of radial ornamentation, I, J, enlargement of the umbonal part to show details of the beak (I) and fine capillation anterior to the protegular node (J). All SEM." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/190403/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

